## 3. Formatting Guidelines

### 3.1 Emoji Usage

**Common Emojis by Section:**
- 🚀 Quick Deploy / Getting Started
- ✨ Features
- 📋 Prerequisites / Lists
- 🔧 Installation / Configuration
- 🎯 Usage
- 🏗️ Architecture
- 🤝 Contributing
- 📄 License
- 🐛 Bugs
- 🆘 Support
- ⚠️ Disclaimer
- 📱 Mobile/UI
- 🔄 Process/Workflow
- 📊 Analytics/Data
- 🤖 AI/Automation

**Guidelines:**
- Use one emoji per section header
- Choose emojis that match section content
- Be consistent across similar sections
- Don't overuse emojis (max 1 per header)

### 3.2 Code Blocks

**Template:**
```markdown
```bash
# Command example
sf project deploy start --source-dir force-app --target-org MyOrg
```
```

**Guidelines:**
- Always specify language (bash, markdown, json, etc.)
- Use appropriate language tags
- Include comments for clarity
- Format commands for readability

### 3.3 Horizontal Rules

Use `---` to separate major sections:
- After Quick Deploy
- After Features
- After Getting Started
- After Usage
- After Technical Architecture
- After Contributing
- After License
- After Disclaimer

### 3.4 Bold Text

Use bold (`**text**`) for:
- Feature names in bullet lists
- Step titles in numbered lists
- Key terms and concepts
- Important warnings or notes
- License type

### 3.5 Blockquotes

Use blockquotes (`>`) for:
- Tagline/description at top
- Important notes or warnings
- Optional deployment notes

